# Pew dbt source freshness overlay

Extends [agent-source-freshness](agent-source-freshness.mdc) for Pew Digital Data Mart (`ddm-dbt`).

## Orchestration and warehouse

- Loads run via **Civis** (`pewdigital/civis-dbt` image) into **Redshift** — copy `warn_after` / `error_after` from a sibling source with the same Civis cadence.
- Confirm in Civis before `error_after` fires in prod on new checks.
- Redshift/Civis context: `redshift-civis.mdc`

## Existing freshness in this repo

- Sitecore: 2 tables (`models/communications/sitecore/staging/sitecore.yml`)
- SFMC: 3 tables (`models/communications/sfmc/base/sfmc.yml`)
- DDM segments: `user_segments` only (`models/communications/ddm_segment_scripts/staging/ddm_segment_scripts.yml`)

GA4 and other imports: confirm load cadence and timestamp column before adding freshness.

## Runbooks and audit

- Adding sources: `docs/runbooks/adding-a-new-source.md`
- Freshness guidance: `docs/dbt_assessment_audit.md` (freshness section)
- Example blocker: `segment_metadata` has no suitable timestamp — document skip in PR/YAML instead of guessing.
